[start section id="20102"]

Metastatic colon cancer, recent metastasis to duodenum

[end section id="20102"]

[start section id="20103"]

A 44-year-old lady with a history of right-sided colon cancer who had right hemicolectomy in 2005. Thereafter she underwent hysterectomy with bilateral oophorectomy for metastatic mucinous adenocarcinoma of ovary as well as peritoneal implants. She underwent resection of a peritoneal implant with resection of a portion of the vagina and closure of vaginal defect and a liver biopsy on 1/16/2007 by Dr. Ostrowski. She has had recurrent small-bowel obstructions since her surgery and underwent  Lysis of adhesions with side-to-side enteroenterostomy on 6/26/2007. Since then she received chemotherapy with disease being stable up until recently when she has been found to have a small mass near the lower edge of the duodenum. Therefore she is admitted for Colectomy with anastomosis along with duodenal resection for the metastasis.

[end section id="20103"]

